window.bookSummaryJSON = "<b>Set Norse-inspired world, and packed with myth, magic, and vengeance, <i>The Shadow of the Gods </i>begins an epic fantasy saga from bestselling author John Gwynne. </b><br><br> A century has passed since the gods fought and drove themselves to extinction. Now only their bones remain, promising great power to those brave enough to seek them out.<br><br> As whispers of war echo across the land of Vigrid, fate follows in the footsteps of three warriors: a huntress on a dangerous quest, a noblewoman pursuing battle fame, and a thrall seeking vengeance among the mercenaries known as the Bloodsworn.<br><br> All three will shape the fate of the world as it once more falls under the shadow of the gods.<br><br> \"A masterfully crafted, brutally compelling Norse-inspired epic.\" —Anthony Ryan <i>The Greatest Sagas Are Written in Blood</i><br><br> For more from John Gwynne, check out: <br><br><u>The Bloodsworn Trilogy</u><br><i>The Shadow of the Gods <br> The Hunger of the Gods <br> The Fury of the Gods </i><br><br><u>Of Blood and Bone</u><br><i>A Time of Dread <br> A Time of Blood <br> A Time of Courage </i><br><br><u>The Faithful and the Fallen</u><br><i>Malice <br> Valor <br> Ruin <br> Wrath</i>"; 
